1
00:00:11,010 --> 00:00:12,680
REED:<i> ECHO II</i> IS AWAY, SIR.

2
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:15,307
A CLEAN LAUNCH.

3
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:18,059
T'POL: IT'S MADE CONTACT
WITH<i> ECHO I.</i>

4
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:20,771
HOW LONG BEFORE WE GET
SUBSPACE ONLINE?

5
00:00:20,813 --> 00:00:22,857
HOSHI: I'D LIKE TO SEND
A FEW TEST TRANSMISSIONS

6
00:00:22,898 --> 00:00:24,441
TO CALIBRATE AMPLIFIERS.

7
00:00:24,483 --> 00:00:25,901
AN HOUR.

8
00:00:25,943 --> 00:00:27,444
ARCHER: MY GUESS IS WE HAVE
A LOT OF PEOPLE ON BOARD

9
00:00:27,486 --> 00:00:28,946
WAITING TO CALL HOME.

10
00:00:28,988 --> 00:00:30,656
[ BEEPING ]

11
00:00:30,698 --> 00:00:33,158
REED: A VESSEL IS DROPPING
OUT OF WARP, CAPTAIN.

12
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,202
12 KILOMETERS DEAD AHEAD.

13
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:37,287
ARCHER: PUT IT UP.

14
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,294
LOOK FAMILIAR?

15
00:00:44,336 --> 00:00:46,839
T'POL: I DON'T RECOGNIZE
THE CONFIGURATION.

16
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:50,049
GOOD. HAIL THEM.

17
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:51,802
[ BEEPING ]

18
00:00:51,844 --> 00:00:54,596
THIS IS THE STARSHIP
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

19
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:56,431
WHAT CAN WE DO FOR YOU?

20
00:01:01,687 --> 00:01:03,480
MY NAME IS JONATHAN ARCHER.

21
00:01:03,522 --> 00:01:05,566
WE'RE ON A MISSION
OF EXPLORATION

22
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:07,860
FROM THE PLANET EARTH.

23
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:12,656
HOSHI?

24
00:01:12,698 --> 00:01:14,575
HOSHI: THE CHANNEL'S OPEN, SIR.

25
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:19,287
DO YOU NEED ASSISTANCE?

26
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:27,671
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO TALK,
THAT'S FINE,

27
00:01:27,713 --> 00:01:31,425
BUT...YOU DROPPED IN ON US.

28
00:01:38,139 --> 00:01:40,601
WAS IT SOMETHING I SAID?

29
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,897
DID YOU GET ANYTHING
ON SENSORS?

30
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:48,191
REED: NO.

31
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,193
ARCHER: "NO" WHAT?

32
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:52,404
NO BIO-SIGNS.

33
00:01:52,446 --> 00:01:55,532
NO PROPULSION,
NO WEAPON SIGNATURES.

34
00:01:55,574 --> 00:01:57,618
NO READINGS AT ALL.

35
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:07,669
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

36
00:02:07,711 --> 00:02:11,006
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

37
00:02:11,048 --> 00:02:14,676
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

38
00:02:14,718 --> 00:02:18,513
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

39
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:23,184
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

40
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:26,647
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

41
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:30,484
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

42
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:33,779
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

43
00:02:33,821 --> 00:02:36,364
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

44
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:38,617
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

45
00:02:38,659 --> 00:02:41,620
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

46
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:46,500
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

47
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:49,419
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

48
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:53,715
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

49
00:02:53,757 --> 00:02:57,052
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

50
00:02:57,094 --> 00:03:02,557
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

51
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,183
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

52
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:06,770
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

53
00:03:06,812 --> 00:03:10,607
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

54
00:03:10,649 --> 00:03:14,778
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

55
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:31,170
ARE THERE ANY INHABITED
SYSTEMS NEARBY?

56
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,796
T'POL: NONE.

57
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:34,756
ARCHER: WHY FLY RIGHT UP TO US
JUST TO GIVE US

58
00:03:34,798 --> 00:03:36,341
THE SILENT TREATMENT?

59
00:03:36,383 --> 00:03:37,926
HOSHI: MAYBE THEY GOT
OUR SIGNAL,

60
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:39,469
BUT IT DIDN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE TO THEM.

61
00:03:39,511 --> 00:03:41,889
OUR TRANSLATOR
IS FAR FROM PERFECT.

62
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,431
T'POL: I WOULDN'T TAKE OFFENSE.

63
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:44,850
NOT EVERY SPECIES HAS MOTIVES

64
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:47,019
THAT CAN BE UNDERSTOOD
IN HUMAN TERMS.

65
00:03:47,061 --> 00:03:48,729
MAYWEATHER: MAYBE THEY
CHECKED US OUT

66
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:51,148
AND DECIDED WE WEREN'T
VERY INTERESTING.

67
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:53,567
REED: US, NOT INTERESTING?

68
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:58,405
LET'S CALIBRATE
THE SUBSPACE AMPLIFIER.

69
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:02,201
AT LEAST THE PEOPLE BACK HOME
WANT TO TALK TO US.

70
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,953
HOSHI: [ CLEARS THROAT ]
SIR?

71
00:04:04,995 --> 00:04:06,914
[ WHISPERING ]
I tracked them down.

72
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:09,583
It took me all week.

73
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:10,918
Archer: Where are they?

74
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:13,420
Hoshi: Kota Baharu--
it's in Malaysia.

75
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,047
Archer: What time is it there?

76
00:04:15,089 --> 00:04:17,049
Hoshi: A little after
9:00 at night.

77
00:04:17,091 --> 00:04:19,051
Archer: That shouldn't be
too late.

78
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:21,095
Let's break in
that new amplifier.

79
00:04:21,136 --> 00:04:23,138
I'll be in my ready room.

80
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:28,060
<i>WOMAN: IS HE ALL RIGHT?</i> 
ARCHER: HE'S FINE.

81
00:04:28,102 --> 00:04:30,020
<i>MAN: IS HE IN SOME KIND</i>
<i>OF TROUBLE?</i>

82
00:04:30,062 --> 00:04:32,689
[ CHUCKLING ] NO, SIR.
MALCOLM'S DOING A GREAT JOB.

83
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:35,483
I'M SURE YOU KNOW IT'S HIS
BIRTHDAY IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

84
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:38,195
<i>WOMAN: YES. YES, IT IS.</i>
<i>SEPTEMBER 2nd.</i>

85
00:04:38,237 --> 00:04:40,822
<i>MAN: WE HAVEN'T SEEN OUR SON</i>
<i>ON HIS BIRTHDAY</i>

86
00:04:40,864 --> 00:04:42,574
<i>FOR QUITE A FEW YEARS.</i>

87
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,534
<i>WOMAN: HE CALLED FROM</i>
<i>SAN FRANCISCO TO LET US KNOW</i>

88
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:46,369
<i>HE'D BEEN ASSIGNED TO</i>
ENTERPRISE,

89
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:50,331
<i>BUT WE HAVEN'T HEARD</i>
<i>FROM HIM SINCE.</i>

90
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:53,627
<i>MAN: WHAT ARE MALCOLM'S DUTIES</i>
<i>ON YOUR SHIP, CAPTAIN?</i>

91
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:55,712
HE'S MY ARMORY OFFICER.

92
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:59,800
<i>MAN: WELL. HIS GRANDFATHER</i>
<i>WOULD BE PLEASED.</i>

93
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:03,262
<i>HE WAS AN ORDNANCE OFFICER</i>
<i>HIMSELF IN THE ROYAL NAVY.</i>

94
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,472
ARCHER: IT MUST BE
IN MALCOLM'S BLOOD.

95
00:05:05,513 --> 00:05:08,100
<i>WOMAN: THE REEDS HAVE BEEN</i>
<i>NAVY MEN FOR GENERATIONS.</i>

96
00:05:08,142 --> 00:05:11,728
<i>MAN: UNTIL MALCOLM DECIDED</i>
<i>TO JOIN THE STARFLEET.</i>

97
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:14,273
<i>I SUPPOSE THE OCEAN</i>
<i>WASN'T BIG ENOUGH FOR HIM.</i>

98
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:18,735
HE'S A LONG WAY FROM HOME,
IN ANY CASE, MR. REED.

99
00:05:18,777 --> 00:05:20,988
I'D LIKE TO DO SOMETHING
FOR HIS BIRTHDAY,

100
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:22,906
MAKE HIM A SPECIAL DINNER.

101
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:25,492
I WAS HOPING YOU COULD TELL ME
WHAT HE LIKES TO EAT.

102
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:28,536
<i>WOMAN: CAPTAIN, MALCOLM'S</i>
<i>NEVER BEEN COMFORTABLE</i>

103
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:31,123
<i>MAKING REQUESTS.</i>

104
00:05:31,165 --> 00:05:33,416
I'M NOT SURE I UNDERSTAND.

105
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,253
<i>MAN: HE ALWAYS ATE WHATEVER</i>
<i>WAS PUT IN FRONT OF HIM.</i>

106
00:05:36,295 --> 00:05:39,673
ARE YOU SAYING HE DOESN'T HAVE
A FAVORITE FOOD?

107
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:42,467
<i>WOMAN: NOT THAT HE'S EVER</i>
<i>TOLD ME.</i>

108
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:47,472
WELL...

109
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:49,474
IF YOU HAPPEN TO THINK
OF ANYTHING,

110
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:51,852
YOU CAN ALWAYS CONTACT ME
THROUGH STARFLEET.

111
00:05:51,893 --> 00:05:54,188
<i>WOMAN: GIVE MALCOLM OUR BEST.</i>

112
00:05:54,229 --> 00:05:55,939
I WILL.

113
00:05:55,981 --> 00:05:58,733
<i>MAN: SAFE JOURNEY, CAPTAIN.</i>

114
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:02,654
[ BEEPING ]

115
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:19,087
HOSHI: HOW'D IT GO?

116
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:20,672
ARCHER: COULD'VE GONE BETTER.

117
00:06:20,714 --> 00:06:23,800
APPARENTLY, HE HASN'T CALLED
HOME SINCE WE LEFT EARTH.

118
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:25,844
I WANT YOU TO FIND OUT
WHAT HE LIKES TO EAT.

119
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:27,054
ME, SIR?

120
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:28,680
ARCHER: BUT DON'T LET
MALCOLM KNOW.

121
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:30,932
HOSHI: MAYBE THIS IS MORE
IN CHEF'S AREA.

122
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:33,434
NO, WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
A DELICATE ASSIGNMENT, HOSHI.

123
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:35,229
IT NEEDS YOUR FINESSE.

124
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:36,980
SIR, I'M RUNNING
A DIAGNOSTIC ON

125
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:39,649
OUR SUBSPACE
TRANSCEIVER ARRAY.

126
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:42,903
GET SOME HELP IF YOU NEED IT,
BUT MAKE THIS A TOP PRIORITY.

127
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:45,822
THAT'S AN ORDER.

128
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:47,908
HOSHI: YES, SIR.

129
00:06:54,373 --> 00:06:55,999
ARCHER: WHERE WERE YOU
AT DINNER?

130
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:57,251
TUCKER: I ATE IN MY QUARTERS.

131
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:58,752
NOW THAT WE'VE GOT
THE AMPLIFIER WORKING,

132
00:06:58,793 --> 00:07:00,587
I WANTED TO ANSWER
A FEW LETTERS.

133
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:03,506
ARCHER: YOU MISSED T'POL'S
LATEST BOUT WITH CHOPSTICKS.

134
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:05,550
TUCKER: DAMN, DINNER AND A SHOW.

135
00:07:05,592 --> 00:07:07,261
[ ARCHER CHUCKLES ]

136
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:11,181
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GONNA UPGRADE THIS.

137
00:07:11,223 --> 00:07:12,515
THAT IS THE UPGRADE.

138
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:16,937
WELL, IF YOU WANT,
I CAN CHANGE THE COLOR.

139
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:20,399
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

140
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,109
ARCHER: WHAT'S THE WORD
FROM HOME?

141
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:24,736
TUCKER: OH, THE USUAL--
ENGINEERING UPDATES.

142
00:07:24,778 --> 00:07:27,655
OH, AND DUVALL GOT PROMOTED.

143
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,616
THEY'RE GIVING HIM
THE<i> SHENANDOAH.</i>

144
00:07:29,657 --> 00:07:32,577
ARCHER: DUVALL GOT
HIS OWN COMMAND?

145
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:35,205
THANK GOD WE'RE
100 LIGHT-YEARS AWAY.

146
00:07:35,247 --> 00:07:37,082
[ CHUCKLING ]

147
00:07:37,124 --> 00:07:39,876
AND I GOT A LETTER
FROM NATALIE.

148
00:07:41,253 --> 00:07:43,380
ARCHER: <i> THE</i> NATALIE,
FROM PENSACOLA?

149
00:07:43,422 --> 00:07:44,714
YEP.

150
00:07:44,756 --> 00:07:47,134
NATALIE FROM PENSACOLA.

151
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:50,804
LOOKS LIKE WE'VE GOT A CHARGE
IMBALANCE IN THIS MANIFOLD.

152
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:53,514
I'LL GET RIGHT ON IT.

153
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:58,437
TRIP?

154
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:02,399
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY LONG-DISTANCE
RELATIONSHIPS NEVER WORK.

155
00:08:02,441 --> 00:08:07,362
WELL...THIS IS ABOUT
AS LONG DISTANCE AS YOU CAN GET.

156
00:08:09,239 --> 00:08:10,615
ARE YOU OK?

157
00:08:11,783 --> 00:08:13,660
OH, YEAH. I JUST--

158
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:15,745
I JUST WISH I'D HAVE
HAD THE CHANCE

159
00:08:15,787 --> 00:08:17,872
TO SAY GOODBYE FACE-TO-FACE.

160
00:08:28,008 --> 00:08:29,468
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

161
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:30,593
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

162
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:32,471
DO YOU SPEND MUCH TIME
WITH MALCOLM?

163
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:34,348
TUCKER: I WAS IN THE ARMORY
YESTERDAY FOR A FEW HOURS,

164
00:08:34,389 --> 00:08:36,224
SWAPPING OUT SOME POWER RELAYS.

165
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:38,559
ARCHER: YOU TALK ABOUT
ANYTHING INTERESTING?

166
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:41,021
TUCKER: POWER RELAYS.

167
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:43,023
ARCHER: I TALKED TO HIS PARENTS
THIS MORNING.

168
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:45,108
TUCKER: REALLY?
ARCHER: YEAH.

169
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,985
STAY HERE.

170
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,323
IF I ASKED YOUR PARENTS
WHAT YOU LIKE TO EAT,

171
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:52,907
WOULD THEY BE ABLE
TO TELL ME?

172
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,493
TUCKER: ARE YOU KIDDING?

173
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:56,870
MY MOM WOULD GIVE YOU HER RECIPE
FOR PAN-FRIED CATFISH

174
00:08:56,911 --> 00:08:58,246
AND WOULDN'T LET YOU GO
TILL YOU PROMISED

175
00:08:58,288 --> 00:08:59,456
NOT TO SCREW IT UP.

176
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:01,291
[ ARCHER CHUCKLES ]

177
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:04,211
ARCHER: MALCOLM'S PARENTS DIDN'T
KNOW WHAT HIS FAVORITE FOOD WAS.

178
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:07,172
THEY DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
HE WAS AN ARMORY OFFICER.

179
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:09,216
TUCKER: THAT'S STRANGE.

180
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:10,675
ARCHER: IT MADE ME THINK.

181
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:14,012
WE DON'T KNOW THAT MUCH
ABOUT MALCOLM, DO WE?

182
00:09:14,054 --> 00:09:16,390
[ RUMBLING ]

183
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:18,808
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
T'Pol: Bridge to the Captain.

184
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:20,018
GO AHEAD.

185
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:22,937
T'Pol: The alien vessel
has returned.

186
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:34,866
ARCHER: GUESS WE WEREN'T
SO UNINTERESTING AFTER ALL.

187
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:37,536
T'POL: THEY DROPPED OUT OF WARP
500 KILOMETERS, DEAD AHEAD.

188
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:39,371
MAYWEATHER: I HAD TO
REVERSE ENGINES

189
00:09:39,413 --> 00:09:41,206
TO KEEP FROM
BANGING INTO THEM.

190
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:43,458
ARCHER: LET'S TRY THIS AGAIN.

191
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,835
[ BEEPING ]

192
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:48,088
WELCOME BACK.

193
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:55,220
I WAS HOPING WE'D HAVE
AN OPPORTUNITY TO MEET AGAIN.

194
00:09:55,262 --> 00:09:59,057
THE PRIMARY MISSION OF MY SHIP
IS TO MAKE PEACEFUL CONTACT

195
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:01,560
WITH OTHER SPECIES.

196
00:10:04,438 --> 00:10:09,192
IF THERE'S ANYTHING WE CAN DO TO
ASSURE YOU OF OUR INTENTIONS...

197
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:20,703
WELL...

198
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:23,164
IT'S BEEN NICE TALKING TO YOU.

199
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:25,750
LET'S DO THIS AGAIN SOMETIME.

200
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:27,252
HOSHI: I'M PICKING UP SOMETHING.

201
00:10:27,294 --> 00:10:28,920
CAN YOU TRANSLATE IT?

202
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:30,671
HOSHI: I--I DON'T THINK
IT'S A LANGUAGE.

203
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:33,341
[ SHRILL NOISE ]
[ ALL GROANING ]

204
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,512
WE'RE BEING SCANNED.

205
00:10:42,434 --> 00:10:44,144
[ GRUNTS ]

206
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:45,770
HULL PLATING?

207
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,897
IT'S OFF-LINE!

208
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:52,819
HARD ABOUT!

209
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:55,405
MAYWEATHER: THEY'VE GONE
TO WARP, SIR.

210
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:58,575
[ BEEPING ]

211
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,495
EVERYBODY OK?

212
00:11:01,536 --> 00:11:02,703
[ BEEPING ]

213
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:05,206
REED: DAMAGE REPORTS
ARE COMING IN, SIR.

214
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:06,874
NO ONE'S BEEN HURT.

215
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,960
ARCHER: WHAT THE HELL
WAS THAT ABOUT?

216
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:10,295
REED: CAPTAIN?

217
00:11:10,337 --> 00:11:11,712
WHEN THEY FIRED THEIR WEAPON,

218
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:13,714
THEY DROPPED THEIR SHIELDING
FOR ABOUT TWO SECONDS.

219
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,967
I WAS ABLE TO TAKE SOME SCANS.

220
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:17,302
WHAT DID YOU GET?

221
00:11:17,344 --> 00:11:20,514
BIO-SIGNS--
AT LEAST 15, MAYBE MORE.

222
00:11:20,555 --> 00:11:23,517
THEIR DNA DOESN'T MATCH ANYTHING
IN OUR DATABASE.

223
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:25,310
REED: IT'S A GOOD THING
THEY'RE GONE.

224
00:11:25,352 --> 00:11:26,603
I DOUBT VERY MUCH
OUR TORPEDOES

225
00:11:26,645 --> 00:11:28,647
COULD'VE PENETRATED
THEIR SHIELDING.

226
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:32,317
STAY ON LONG-RANGE SCANNERS.

227
00:11:32,359 --> 00:11:35,445
IF THEY COME ANYWHERE NEAR US,
I WANT TO KNOW.

228
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:37,447
T'POL.

229
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:46,456
TUCKER: THAT SUPPORT FRAME'S
BENT.

230
00:11:46,498 --> 00:11:49,459
WE'LL NEED TO REINFORCE IT. 

231
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,590
ARCHER: HOW BAD IS IT?

232
00:11:55,632 --> 00:11:57,467
TUCKER: IF THAT LAST SHOT HAD
BEEN ABOUT A HALF-METER HIGHER,

233
00:11:57,509 --> 00:11:58,759
WE'D BE LOOKING AT STARS.

234
00:11:58,801 --> 00:12:00,387
ARCHER: HOLD IT A MINUTE.

235
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:02,305
THERE WERE 13 PEOPLE WORKING
IN THIS SECTION, CAPTAIN,

236
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:04,307
INCLUDING YOURS TRULY.

237
00:12:05,308 --> 00:12:07,143
IF THAT BULKHEAD HAD BLOWN...

238
00:12:07,185 --> 00:12:09,770
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

239
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:12,065
ARCHER: DID YOUR PEOPLE RUN INTO
AS MANY HOSTILE ALIENS

240
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:14,817
WHEN THEY FIRST WENT
INTO DEEP SPACE?

241
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,778
T'POL: IT WAS A DIFFERENT TIME.

242
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,531
ARCHER: HOW SO?

243
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,991
T'POL: THERE WERE FEWER
WARP-CAPABLE SPECIES.

244
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,910
ARCHER: THIS SHIP
JUST ISN'T EQUIPPED TO HANDLE

245
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:26,787
SOME OF THE THREATS
WE'RE COMING UP AGAINST.

246
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:28,915
IT'S TIME WE DO
SOMETHING ABOUT THAT.

247
00:12:28,956 --> 00:12:30,709
T'POL: WHAT ARE YOU SUGGESTING?

248
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:33,461
ARCHER:<i> ENTERPRISE</i> WAS FITTED
WITH PHASE CANNON PORTS.

249
00:12:33,503 --> 00:12:35,589
BUT SINCE WE LEFT SPACEDOCK
A FEW WEEKS AHEAD OF SCHEDULE,

250
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:38,299
THE CANNONS
WERE NEVER INSTALLED.

251
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:43,762
I THINK IT'S TIME THEY WERE.

252
00:12:43,804 --> 00:12:46,266
WE SHOULD HEAD BACK TO EARTH.

253
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:48,101
JUST GIVE US TWO WEEKS, CAPTAIN.

254
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:49,519
TUCKER: I KNOW WE CAN DO IT.

255
00:12:49,561 --> 00:12:51,396
MOST OF THE STUFF WE NEED
IS ALREADY ON THE SHIP.

256
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:53,273
ARCHER: THE ARMORY TEAM
AT JUPITER STATION

257
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,191
IS TRAINED FOR
THIS KIND OF WORK.

258
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:57,485
IF WE'RE GONNA DO THIS,
LET'S DO IT RIGHT.

259
00:12:57,527 --> 00:12:59,404
TUCKER: MY ENGINEERS ARE
JUST AS GOOD AS THEY ARE.

260
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:01,155
ARCHER: I KNOW THAT, TRIP.

261
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:04,492
BUT WE HAVE OTHER SYSTEMS
THAT COULD USE OVERHAULS.

262
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:08,371
LOOK AT THE BRIGHT SIDE.

263
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:12,125
YOU'VE GOT A CHANCE
TO SAY GOODBYE TO NATALIE.

264
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:13,834
REED: SIR?

265
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:16,045
WITH YOUR PERMISSION, WE COULD
AT LEAST BEGIN THE WORK,

266
00:13:16,087 --> 00:13:18,047
GET A FEW THINGS STARTED
FOR JUPITER STATION.

267
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,716
TUCKER: IT'LL CUT DOWN THE TIME

268
00:13:19,758 --> 00:13:21,551
WE'LL HAVE TO SPEND
IN SPACEDOCK.

269
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,929
DO WHAT YOU CAN.

270
00:13:26,473 --> 00:13:28,266
[ BEEPS ]
ARCHER TO MAYWEATHER.

271
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:30,143
Mayweather: Go ahead, Captain.

272
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:34,522
WE'RE HEADING HOME.

273
00:13:54,334 --> 00:13:56,294
REED: THIS, LADIES
AND GENTLEMEN,

274
00:13:56,336 --> 00:13:59,255
IS A PHASE-MODULATED
ENERGY WEAPON.

275
00:13:59,297 --> 00:14:02,342
IT'S RATED FOR A MAXIMUM
POWER OUTPUT

276
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,594
OF 500 GIGAJOULES.

277
00:14:04,636 --> 00:14:07,639
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> WAS DESIGNED
TO CARRY THREE OF THEM.

278
00:14:07,681 --> 00:14:11,309
WE HAVE ONE, AND IT'S
ONLY A PROTOTYPE.

279
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:13,687
TUCKER: OUR JOB IS TO GET IT
UP AND RUNNING

280
00:14:13,728 --> 00:14:15,689
AND BUILD TWO MORE
FROM SCRATCH.

281
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:18,107
THE CAPTAIN IS TAKING US BACK
BECAUSE HE THINKS

282
00:14:18,149 --> 00:14:21,068
THIS WORK OUGHT TO BE DONE
BY THE BOYS IN SPACEDOCK.

283
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:23,530
REED: FAR BE IT FROM ME TO
QUESTION THE CAPTAIN'S JUDGMENT,

284
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:25,198
BUT COMMANDER TUCKER
AND I BELIEVE

285
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:26,783
WE CAN DO THIS OURSELVES.

286
00:14:26,825 --> 00:14:28,409
TUCKER: THAT MEANS
DOUBLE SHIFTS.

287
00:14:28,451 --> 00:14:31,579
BY THE TIME WE REACH
JUPITER STATION,

288
00:14:31,621 --> 00:14:33,665
I DON'T WANT THEIR ENGINEERS
TO HAVE A THING TO DO

289
00:14:33,707 --> 00:14:35,249
BUT GIVE US A WASH AND A WAX.

290
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,627
[ ENGINEERS CHUCKLE ]
ANY QUESTIONS?

291
00:14:37,669 --> 00:14:40,087
ARE WE EXPECTING
ANOTHER ATTACK, SIR?

292
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:42,923
TUCKER: WE ALL SIGNED UP
FOR THIS TRIP BECAUSE WE WANTED

293
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,510
TO DO SOMETHING NO ONE
HAD EVER DONE BEFORE,

294
00:14:45,552 --> 00:14:48,137
NOT BECAUSE WE THOUGHT
IT'D BE EASY

295
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:50,056
OR SAFE.

296
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:53,100
BUT WE'RE NOT HERE
TO TAKE FOOLISH RISKS.

297
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:54,686
THE CAPTAIN
AND THE REST OF THE CREW

298
00:14:54,728 --> 00:14:56,396
ARE DEPENDING ON US
TO KEEP<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

299
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:57,814
READY FOR ANYTHING.

300
00:14:57,856 --> 00:15:00,775
REED: AND ONCE WE GET
THESE PHASE CANNONS ONLINE,

301
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:04,945
WE'LL HAVE A LOT MORE FIREPOWER
TO DO JUST THAT.

302
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:08,867
TUCKER: SO WHAT ARE YOU
STANDING AROUND FOR?

303
00:15:11,828 --> 00:15:14,789
<i>HE ONCE TOLD ME</i>
<i>THAT HE LOVED TO EAT OCTOPUS,</i>

304
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:16,875
<i>ESPECIALLY</i>
<i>THE LITTLE SUCTION CUPS,</i>

305
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,626
<i>BUT I THINK</i>
<i>HE WAS PULLING MY LEG.</i>

306
00:15:18,668 --> 00:15:22,589
<i>YOU CAN NEVER TELL WHETHER</i>
<i>MY BROTHER'S JOKING OR NOT.</i>

307
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:24,632
<i>CAN I TALK TO HIM?</i>

308
00:15:24,674 --> 00:15:27,844
WE REALLY WOULD LIKE
TO KEEP THIS A SURPRISE.

309
00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:29,763
<i>OH, RIGHT. THE DINNER.</i>

310
00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:33,767
<i>I REMEMBER ONE TIME--THIS</i>
<i>WAS AT LEAST 10 YEARS AGO--</i>

311
00:15:33,808 --> 00:15:35,518
<i>HE WENT FOR A WHOLE WEEK</i>
<i>WITHOUT EATING.</i>

312
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:37,103
HOSHI: REALLY?

313
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:39,773
<i>GOT BY ON NOTHING BUT WATER</i>
<i>AND A LITTLE APPLE JUICE.</i>

314
00:15:39,814 --> 00:15:40,981
WHY?

315
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:42,859
<i>SOME SORT OF SURVIVAL TRAINING,</i>

316
00:15:42,901 --> 00:15:45,236
<i>OR WAS IT A CONTEST?</i>

317
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,613
WHEN HE STARTED EATING AGAIN,

318
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:48,948
DO YOU REMEMBER
THE FIRST THING HE WANTED?

319
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:51,534
<i>HE WAS SO WEAK,</i>
<i>HE COULD BARELY GET OUT OF BED.</i>

320
00:15:51,576 --> 00:15:54,120
<i>FOR TWO DAYS, ALL HE HAD</i>
<i>WAS PROTEIN CONCENTRATE.</i>

321
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:56,414
HOSHI: WHEN YOU TWO
WERE GROWING UP,

322
00:15:56,456 --> 00:15:58,750
HE NEVER SAID,
"HEY, LET'S GO OUT FOR PIZZA,"

323
00:15:58,792 --> 00:16:03,129
OR, "BOY, I'D LOVE
SOME INDIAN FOOD"?

324
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:05,506
<i>NOT THAT I REMEMBER.</i>

325
00:16:05,548 --> 00:16:08,843
<i>MALCOLM ISN'T THE EASIEST</i>
<i>PERSON TO GET TO KNOW.</i>

326
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:12,597
I'M FIGURING THAT OUT.

327
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:14,223
<i>WHEN WE WERE TRAINING</i>
<i>IN SAN FRANCISCO,</i>

328
00:16:14,265 --> 00:16:16,225
<i>THERE WAS A LITTLE RESTAURANT</i>
<i>ON THE EMBARCADERO</i>

329
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:17,811
<i>HE LIKED TO GO TO.</i>

330
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:20,814
<i>THEY HAD A SPECIALTY--</i>
<i>SOME KIND OF...FISH, I THINK.</i>

331
00:16:20,855 --> 00:16:22,816
WHAT KIND?

332
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:24,609
HALIBUT?

333
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:25,735
UH, SWORDFISH?

334
00:16:25,777 --> 00:16:26,945
<i>NO.</i>

335
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,739
MAHIMAHI? SCALLOPS?

336
00:16:29,781 --> 00:16:31,783
<i>I HAD SEA BASS.</i>

337
00:16:31,825 --> 00:16:33,993
GREAT! AND MALCOLM?

338
00:16:34,034 --> 00:16:35,578
<i>I DON'T REMEMBER.</i>

339
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,831
TRY, PLEASE.

340
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:40,124
<i>MAUREEN.</i>

341
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:42,168
IS THAT A FISH?

342
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:43,920
<i>NO, SHE WAS THE WAITRESS.</i>

343
00:16:43,962 --> 00:16:45,505
[<i> CHUCKLING</i> ]

344
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:47,256
<i>THAT'S WHY MALCOLM WANTED</i>
<i>TO GO THERE!</i>

345
00:16:47,298 --> 00:16:48,842
<i>HE HAD A THING FOR HER!</i>

346
00:16:48,883 --> 00:16:50,510
<i>I THINK HE HATES FISH.</i>

347
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:51,845
HOSHI: THANKS.

348
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:53,554
[ BEEPS ]

349
00:16:57,851 --> 00:17:01,813
SO HOW'S YOUR
SECRET MISSION COMING?

350
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:05,107
HOSHI: I'VE TALKED TO HIS
SISTER, HIS BEST FRIEND,

351
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:07,527
HIS UNCLE ARCHIE,
HIS TWO SPINSTER AUNTS.

352
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,195
THE MOST ANYONE SEEMS
TO KNOW ABOUT HIS

353
00:17:09,236 --> 00:17:12,156
EATING HABITS IS THAT
HE...OCCASIONALLY EATS.

354
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:14,826
[ MAYWEATHER CHUCKLES ]
T'POL: ENSIGN?

355
00:17:14,868 --> 00:17:17,495
IF YOU WANT TO KNOW SOMETHING
ABOUT MR. REED,

356
00:17:17,537 --> 00:17:19,580
PERHAPS YOU SHOULD ASK HIM.

357
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:36,014
HOSHI: ANYONE SITTING HERE?

358
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,431
REED: UH, NO.

359
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:39,517
PLEASE.

360
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:40,935
HOSHI: OOH.

361
00:17:40,977 --> 00:17:43,771
THIS IS THE FIRST CHANCE
I'VE HAD TO EAT ALL DAY.

362
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:45,023
REED: OHH.

363
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,691
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

364
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:50,570
I HAVEN'T SET FOOT OUTSIDE
THE ARMORY SINCE 0700.

365
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:53,573
HOSHI: HOW'S YOUR RAVIOLI?

366
00:17:53,614 --> 00:17:55,742
REED: YEAH, IT'S FINE.

367
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:59,913
HOSHI: NOTHING LIKE
A NICE PLATE OF PASTA.

368
00:17:59,954 --> 00:18:01,998
REED: MM-HMM.

369
00:18:07,962 --> 00:18:10,048
YOU KNOW,
I USED TO LOVE TO COOK,

370
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:11,841
BUT I NEVER GET
A CHANCE TO ANYMORE--

371
00:18:11,883 --> 00:18:14,594
THE WAY THAT CHEF
PROTECTS THE GALLEY.

372
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:21,392
ONE OF THESE NIGHTS,
I SHOULD FIX SOMETHING MYSELF.

373
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:23,352
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

374
00:18:23,394 --> 00:18:25,563
REED: I'M SORRY.

375
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:27,857
HOSHI: YOU'D LOVE MY ENCHILADAS.

376
00:18:27,899 --> 00:18:30,026
REED: ENCHILADAS?

377
00:18:30,068 --> 00:18:32,946
HOSHI: WELL, IF YOU DON'T LIKE
THEM, I CAN FIX SOMETHING ELSE.

378
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:37,658
WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE FOOD?

379
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:40,244
[ SCOFFS ]

380
00:18:40,286 --> 00:18:41,829
UH, I APPRECIATE THE OFFER,

381
00:18:41,871 --> 00:18:45,291
BUT IT--
IT REALLY ISN'T NECESSARY.

382
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,168
HOSHI: AREN'T YOU GETTING
A LITTLE TIRED

383
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:51,505
OF HAVING TO EAT WHATEVER
CHEF HAPPENS TO SERVE?

384
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:53,883
REED: NO, HE'S A--
HE'S A FINE COOK.

385
00:18:53,925 --> 00:18:55,927
HOSHI: DON'T GET ME WRONG.
HE'S TERRIFIC.

386
00:18:55,969 --> 00:18:59,597
IT'S JUST THAT DINNER
IN THE MESS HALL CAN...

387
00:18:59,639 --> 00:19:01,766
LACK A CERTAIN
PERSONAL TOUCH.

388
00:19:01,808 --> 00:19:04,560
I'VE GOT A HOT PLATE
IN MY QUARTERS.

389
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:12,401
THAT'S...VERY FLATTERING AND...

390
00:19:12,443 --> 00:19:15,529
I'M JUST NOT SURE IT
WOULD BE APPROPRIATE.

391
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:17,448
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

392
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:21,661
WELL, UM...WE WORK
TOGETHER AND, UH,

393
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:25,498
IT JUST MIGHT BE
A LITTLE...AWKWARD--

394
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:27,458
SERVING ON THE SAME SHIP.

395
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:30,461
HOSHI: WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH...

396
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:33,380
OH.
[ LAUGHING ]

397
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:37,051
NO, I DIDN'T--
I DIDN'T MEAN TO, UM...

398
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:41,221
IMPLY ANYTHING OTHER THAN
JUST MAKING DINNER, LIEUTENANT.

399
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:42,807
REED: THEN, UH,
IT'S MY MISTAKE, ENSIGN.

400
00:19:42,849 --> 00:19:46,268
HOSHI: NO, UH, IT'S MY FAULT.
I SHOULDN'T HAVE...

401
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:47,854
YEAH, I'LL--I'LL JUST--

402
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:49,396
REED: NO, NO.
PLEASE, FINISH YOUR DINNER.

403
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:53,901
HOSHI: NO, NO. YOU'VE GOT
A LOT OF WORK TO DO, SO...

404
00:19:53,943 --> 00:19:56,529
[ DOOR OPENS ]

405
00:20:08,374 --> 00:20:11,418
CAPTAIN, I'M DETECTING
A SHIP, DEAD ASTERN--

406
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:13,379
8,000 METERS.

407
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:15,422
ARCHER: LET ME GUESS--
OUR SHADOW?

408
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:16,674
[ BEEPING ]

409
00:20:16,716 --> 00:20:18,759
CLOSING TO 7,000.

410
00:20:20,094 --> 00:20:21,804
T'POL: 6,000.

411
00:20:23,139 --> 00:20:24,974
POLARIZE THE HULL PLATING.

412
00:20:25,016 --> 00:20:27,476
[ RUMBLING ]

413
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:37,153
REED TO BRIDGE.

414
00:20:37,195 --> 00:20:39,572
ARMORY, REPORT.

415
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:41,824
GET TO YOUR STATIONS. MOVE.

416
00:20:46,996 --> 00:20:48,622
WARP DRIVE IS OFFLINE.

417
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:52,835
T'POL: MAIN POWER IS DOWN.

418
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:05,472
[ BEEPING ]

419
00:21:05,514 --> 00:21:07,558
ARCHER: TORPEDOES.

420
00:21:10,477 --> 00:21:12,230
TACTICAL SYSTEMS ARE DOWN.

421
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:15,942
ARCHER: WHY DON'T YOU SAVE TIME
AND TELL ME WHAT<i> ISN'T</i> DOWN?

422
00:21:17,235 --> 00:21:19,486
THE OUTER DOORS
IN LAUNCH BAY 2 ARE OPENING.

423
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:21,697
ARCHER: SEAL THEM.
T'POL: I CAN'T.

424
00:21:34,961 --> 00:21:37,379
[ CLATTERING ]

425
00:22:44,155 --> 00:22:45,906
GET AWAY FROM THOSE MEN!

426
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:56,876
[ BEEPING ]

427
00:23:08,679 --> 00:23:10,764
ARCHER: GO.

428
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:12,016
ARCHER TO SICK BAY.

429
00:23:12,058 --> 00:23:13,433
Phlox: Phlox here, Captain.

430
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:16,603
REPORT TO E-DECK, SECTION 7!
THIS IS AN EMERGENCY!

431
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:17,646
Phlox: On my way.

432
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:20,233
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

433
00:23:20,274 --> 00:23:22,235
Crewman: Security
to Captain Archer.

434
00:23:22,276 --> 00:23:23,443
ARCHER: GO AHEAD.

435
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:24,695
Crewman: The aliens
are gone, sir.

436
00:23:24,737 --> 00:23:27,405
They've launched their shuttle.

437
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,460
[ RUMBLING ]

438
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:42,380
BRIDGE, REPORT!

439
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:44,422
T'Pol: The alien vessel
has gone to warp,

440
00:23:44,464 --> 00:23:47,051
but that last shot damaged
our port nacelle.

441
00:23:47,093 --> 00:23:48,969
We're venting drive plasma.

442
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:50,221
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

443
00:23:50,263 --> 00:23:51,555
[ BEEPS ]

444
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,272
ARCHER: DOCTOR?

445
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:01,357
PHLOX: [SIGHS]
I'VE STABILIZED THEM,

446
00:24:01,399 --> 00:24:05,278
BUT THEY WERE SUBJECTED
TO SOME RATHER INVASIVE SCANS.

447
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:09,282
ARCHER: WILL THEY BE ALL RIGHT?

448
00:24:09,323 --> 00:24:11,617
PHLOX: THERE COULD BE SOME
RESIDUAL NEUROLOGICAL DAMAGE.

449
00:24:11,658 --> 00:24:14,287
I'M DOING EVERYTHING I CAN.

450
00:24:14,328 --> 00:24:16,289
ARCHER: HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
OF ANYTHING LIKE THIS?

451
00:24:16,330 --> 00:24:17,915
T'POL: NO.

452
00:24:17,957 --> 00:24:19,292
ARCHER: ARE THERE
ANY VULCAN RECORDS

453
00:24:19,333 --> 00:24:21,459
OF A SPECIES THAT USES
SIMILAR TACTICS?

454
00:24:21,501 --> 00:24:24,380
AND I DON'T CARE HOW CLASSIFIED
THEY MIGHT BE.

455
00:24:24,422 --> 00:24:26,757
T'POL: NONE THAT I KNOW OF,
CAPTAIN.

456
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:31,304
FIND OUT WHAT YOU CAN.

457
00:24:31,345 --> 00:24:34,056
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
Tucker: Tucker to Archer.

458
00:24:35,391 --> 00:24:36,767
GO AHEAD.

459
00:24:36,809 --> 00:24:38,436
TUCKER: WE'VE GOT
THE PLASMA LEAK UNDER CONTROL,

460
00:24:38,476 --> 00:24:40,438
BUT OUR PORT NACELLE
TOOK A LOT OF DAMAGE.

461
00:24:40,478 --> 00:24:42,522
Archer: How long before
we can go to warp?

462
00:24:42,564 --> 00:24:44,524
TUCKER: A COUPLE OF DAYS.

463
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:46,568
ARCHER: WHAT ABOUT
IMPULSE POWER?

464
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:48,279
Tucker: Well, that's
the good news.

465
00:24:48,321 --> 00:24:50,614
IT SHOULD BE BACK ONLINE
IN A FEW MINUTES.

466
00:24:50,656 --> 00:24:53,326
ARCHER: I'LL TAKE
ALL THE GOOD NEWS I CAN GET.

467
00:24:53,367 --> 00:24:55,411
KEEP ME POSTED, DOCTOR.

468
00:24:58,789 --> 00:25:02,376
THERE ARE NO VULCAN SHIPS
WITHIN SCANNING RANGE.

469
00:25:02,418 --> 00:25:05,879
MAYWEATHER: SIR, WE COULD TRY TO
CONTACT THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND.

470
00:25:05,921 --> 00:25:08,506
THEY'RE ONLY TWO DAYS AWAY
AT WARP 6.

471
00:25:08,548 --> 00:25:10,550
I'M SURE THEY'D GIVE US A HAND.

472
00:25:10,592 --> 00:25:12,928
ARCHER: I'M SURE THEY WOULD.

473
00:25:27,276 --> 00:25:28,861
[ ARCHER SIGHS ]

474
00:25:31,238 --> 00:25:33,282
I CAN'T RAISE VULCAN.

475
00:25:33,324 --> 00:25:36,618
IT'S FUNNY--I RAN A DIAGNOSTIC
AFTER THE ATTACK,

476
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,954
BUT NOW<i> ECHO II</i> WON'T RESPOND.

477
00:25:38,996 --> 00:25:40,747
THAT'S BECAUSE IT ISN'T THERE.

478
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:42,124
WHAT?

479
00:25:42,166 --> 00:25:43,459
THERE'S NOTHING BUT DEBRIS
AT THE COORDINATES

480
00:25:43,501 --> 00:25:45,419
WHERE WE DEPLOYED THE AMPLIFIER.

481
00:25:45,461 --> 00:25:48,130
ARCHER: WHAT ABOUT<i> ECHO I?</i>

482
00:25:49,465 --> 00:25:51,425
DESTROYED, AS WELL.

483
00:25:59,433 --> 00:26:02,019
THE STABILIZER ON CANNON PORT 2
CHECKS OUT OK, SIR.

484
00:26:02,061 --> 00:26:03,396
REED: PORT 2 OR PORT 1?

485
00:26:03,437 --> 00:26:04,813
CREWMAN: PORT 1, SIR. SORRY.

486
00:26:04,855 --> 00:26:07,983
REED: GET IT RIGHT!
START ON THOSE BEAM EMITTERS.

487
00:26:08,025 --> 00:26:09,443
CREWMAN: YES, SIR.

488
00:26:09,485 --> 00:26:11,111
TUCKER: TARGETING SCANNERS
WILL BE ONLINE IN AN HOUR.

489
00:26:11,153 --> 00:26:13,655
REED: WE SHOULD BE ALIGNING THEM
BY NOW, NOT INSTALLING THEM.

490
00:26:13,697 --> 00:26:16,574
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

491
00:26:24,291 --> 00:26:26,293
TUCKER: YOU WERE A LITTLE HARD
ON EDDIE.

492
00:26:26,335 --> 00:26:29,463
EVERYONE IS BUSTING THEIR TAILS
TO GET THIS JOB DONE.

493
00:26:29,505 --> 00:26:30,756
REED: AAH!
TUCKER: YOU OK?

494
00:26:30,797 --> 00:26:31,965
REED: YEAH!

495
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:34,176
[ GROANING ]
FINE.

496
00:26:34,218 --> 00:26:36,136
I TOLD THEM TO DEPOLARIZE
THESE RELAYS!

497
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:37,971
TUCKER: WHAT WERE YOU
TRYING TO DO?

498
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:39,390
REED: BYPASS THE E.P.S. GRID.

499
00:26:39,432 --> 00:26:40,766
TUCKER: WHY?

500
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:42,184
REED: WELL, WE COULD DRAW POWER
FOR THE CANNONS

501
00:26:42,226 --> 00:26:43,810
DIRECTLY
FROM THE IMPULSE ENGINES.

502
00:26:43,852 --> 00:26:45,812
ARE YOU TRYING TO MAKE THIS
BLOW UP IN YOUR FACE?

503
00:26:45,854 --> 00:26:48,065
THE RELAYS WERE RATED
TO HANDLE THAT MUCH POWER.

504
00:26:48,107 --> 00:26:49,275
TUCKER: WHAT IF THERE'S A SURGE?

505
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:50,608
REED: OH, I'VE THOUGHT OF THAT.

506
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:52,069
THESE INVERTERS WERE DESIGNED

507
00:26:52,111 --> 00:26:53,862
TO CUT IN AT THE FIRST SIGN
OF AN OVERLOAD.

508
00:26:53,904 --> 00:26:56,323
WE GOT TO DO THIS BY THE BOOK,
OR WE'LL END UP

509
00:26:56,365 --> 00:26:59,326
BLOWING A BIGGER HOLE
IN OURSELVES THAN THE BAD GUYS.

510
00:26:59,368 --> 00:27:01,328
I'VE RUN A DOZEN SIMULATIONS.

511
00:27:01,370 --> 00:27:03,956
IT'S AN ACCEPTABLE RISK.

512
00:27:03,997 --> 00:27:06,917
WHEN IT COMES
TO MODIFYING SHIP SYSTEMS,

513
00:27:06,959 --> 00:27:09,587
WHY DON'T YOU LET
THE CHIEF ENGINEER DECIDE

514
00:27:09,627 --> 00:27:12,256
WHAT'S AN ACCEPTABLE RISK?

515
00:27:12,298 --> 00:27:14,258
SIR...

516
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:17,177
IF WE DO THIS BY THE BOOK,

517
00:27:17,219 --> 00:27:20,222
THOSE ALIENS ARE LIKELY
TO BE BACK BEFORE WE'RE DONE.

518
00:27:20,264 --> 00:27:22,224
TUCKER: I WANT TO GET THIS JOB
DONE AS QUICKLY AS YOU DO,

519
00:27:22,266 --> 00:27:24,851
LIEUTENANT, BUT NOT IF IT MEANS
TAKING SHORTCUTS

520
00:27:24,893 --> 00:27:27,605
THAT COULD GET
OUR PEOPLE KILLED.

521
00:27:29,482 --> 00:27:31,609
REED: YES, SIR.

522
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:35,571
[ FOOTSTEPS RETREAT ]

523
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:40,033
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

524
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:50,794
ARCHER: DON'T YOU EVER REST?

525
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:53,422
TUCKER: YOU KNOW, I CAN'T SLEEP
WITHOUT THE WARP ENGINES ONLINE.

526
00:27:53,464 --> 00:27:55,215
IF I DON'T FEEL
THOSE VIBRATIONS,

527
00:27:55,257 --> 00:27:57,468
SOMETHING JUST
DOESN'T SEEM RIGHT.

528
00:27:57,510 --> 00:28:00,429
WELL, I HOPE YOU GET THEM FIXED
SOON BECAUSE YOU LOOK LIKE HELL.

529
00:28:00,471 --> 00:28:02,264
WELL, WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
CAPTAIN,

530
00:28:02,306 --> 00:28:04,183
YOU SHOULDN'T BE TALKING.

531
00:28:05,476 --> 00:28:07,102
ARCHER: HOW'S IT COMING?

532
00:28:07,144 --> 00:28:08,812
TUCKER: THEY'LL BE ONLINE
BY THE END OF THE DAY TOMORROW,

533
00:28:08,854 --> 00:28:10,730
GUARANTEED.

534
00:28:12,316 --> 00:28:15,110
COULD YOU CHECK
THE DILITHIUM ALIGNMENT FOR ME?

535
00:28:15,152 --> 00:28:16,445
ARCHER: SURE.

536
00:28:23,243 --> 00:28:25,287
ARCHER: .06 MICRONS.

537
00:28:27,164 --> 00:28:30,959
AT LEAST WE'LL BE FLYING HOME
UNDER OUR OWN POWER.

538
00:28:32,127 --> 00:28:34,588
LET ME KNOW
IF IT DROPS BELOW .03.

539
00:28:36,507 --> 00:28:39,092
I TRIED TO GET A MESSAGE
TO THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND,

540
00:28:39,134 --> 00:28:41,053
BUT IT DIDN'T GO THROUGH.

541
00:28:41,094 --> 00:28:45,516
IF IT HAD, WE'D BE EXPECTING
A SURAK-CLASS SHIP TOMORROW,

542
00:28:45,558 --> 00:28:48,394
OH SO POLITELY
OFFERING TO HELP US.

543
00:28:48,435 --> 00:28:50,437
WELL, THE VULCANS
WOULD'VE LOVED THAT--

544
00:28:50,479 --> 00:28:53,106
TOWING THE PRIDE OF STARFLEET
BACK TO BASE.

545
00:28:54,274 --> 00:28:55,817
MAYBE WE SHOULD THANK
OUR VISITORS

546
00:28:55,859 --> 00:28:58,362
FOR BLOWING UP
THE SUBSPACE AMPLIFIERS.

547
00:28:58,404 --> 00:29:00,406
[ BEEPING ]

548
00:29:02,408 --> 00:29:04,243
HOLDING AT .05.

549
00:29:04,284 --> 00:29:06,745
KEEP AN EYE ON IT.

550
00:29:08,288 --> 00:29:10,957
YOU LOOKING FORWARD
TO SEEING EARTH?

551
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:12,834
SURE.

552
00:29:12,876 --> 00:29:16,547
I JUST...DIDN'T THINK
I'D BE SEEING IT SO SOON.

553
00:29:16,589 --> 00:29:18,424
THIS TIME...

554
00:29:18,465 --> 00:29:21,468
WE WON'T BE LEAVING
BEFORE WE'RE READY.

555
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:25,013
ARE YOUR EARS
A LITTLE POINTIER THAN USUAL?

556
00:29:25,055 --> 00:29:27,140
ARCHER: I NEV--

557
00:29:28,601 --> 00:29:31,353
I NEVER SAID
WE DIDN'T BELONG OUT HERE.

558
00:29:31,395 --> 00:29:33,980
I JUST WISH WE'D HAVE...

559
00:29:34,022 --> 00:29:36,816
LAUNCHED WITH ALL
OUR SYSTEMS ONLINE,

560
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:39,069
ESPECIALLY WEAPONS.

561
00:29:39,111 --> 00:29:41,071
IF WE HADN'T LAUNCHED
WHEN WE DID,

562
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:44,658
THEY'D HAVE SENT KLAANG
BACK TO KRONOS IN A BOX.

563
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:47,286
I KEEP REMINDING MYSELF OF THAT.

564
00:29:47,327 --> 00:29:50,247
BUT I RUSHED US OUT OF SPACEDOCK

565
00:29:50,289 --> 00:29:52,666
BECAUSE I HAD
SOMETHING TO PROVE.

566
00:29:52,708 --> 00:29:55,628
AND I RISKED THE LIVES OF...

567
00:29:55,669 --> 00:29:59,757
81 HUMANS, A VULCAN,
AND A DENOBULAN TO DO IT.

568
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:01,467
DON'T FORGET PORTHOS.

569
00:30:01,508 --> 00:30:04,094
[ CHUCKLES ]
THANKS.

570
00:30:05,638 --> 00:30:07,598
IN THE OLD DAYS,
ASTRONAUTS RODE ROCKETS

571
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,266
WITH MILLIONS OF LITERS
OF HYDROGEN

572
00:30:09,308 --> 00:30:10,892
BURNING UNDER THEIR SEATS.

573
00:30:10,934 --> 00:30:12,811
YOU THINK THEY SAID,

574
00:30:12,852 --> 00:30:14,896
"GEE, I'D LOVE TO GO
TO THE MOON TODAY,

575
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:17,232
BUT IT SEEMS A LITTLE RISKY"?

576
00:30:17,274 --> 00:30:20,110
I THINK IF YOU ASKED
ANYONE ON BOARD

577
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:22,279
WHETHER THEY THOUGHT
THIS MISSION WAS WORTH THE RISK,

578
00:30:22,321 --> 00:30:26,116
YOU'D GET THE SAME ANSWER
FROM EVERY ONE OF THEM.

579
00:30:31,997 --> 00:30:34,750
LET ME KNOW
WHEN WE'RE READY TO GO TO WARP.

580
00:30:34,792 --> 00:30:36,876
AYE, SIR.

581
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:47,680
TUCKER: HAVE YOU STILL GOT
THOSE GUNS OF YOURS

582
00:30:47,721 --> 00:30:49,264
HOOKED UP
TO THE IMPULSE ENGINES?

583
00:30:49,306 --> 00:30:50,974
REED: I'M JUST
DISCONNECTING THEM NOW.

584
00:30:51,016 --> 00:30:53,059
TUCKER: HANG ON A MINUTE.

585
00:30:54,978 --> 00:30:56,980
YOU'RE SURE THIS WILL WORK?

586
00:30:57,022 --> 00:30:59,274
REED: YES, COMMANDER, I AM.

587
00:30:59,316 --> 00:31:01,276
TUCKER: THEN, BASED ON
THE RECOMMENDATION

588
00:31:01,318 --> 00:31:02,861
OF THE ARMORY OFFICER,

589
00:31:02,902 --> 00:31:05,947
THE CHIEF ENGINEER FINDS
THE LEVEL OF RISK ACCEPTABLE.

590
00:31:07,533 --> 00:31:09,409
IN THAT CASE,

591
00:31:09,451 --> 00:31:12,496
IF THE CHIEF ENGINEER WOULDN'T
MIND GETTING HIS HANDS DIRTY,

592
00:31:12,538 --> 00:31:14,498
I COULD USE SOME HELP.

593
00:31:18,126 --> 00:31:22,088
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
SEPTEMBER 1, 2151.

594
00:31:22,130 --> 00:31:25,300
IT'S BEEN TWO DAYS NOW WITH
NO SIGN OF THE ALIEN VESSEL.

595
00:31:25,342 --> 00:31:27,927
MY CREW HAS MANAGED TO DO
IN 48 HOURS

596
00:31:27,969 --> 00:31:30,180
WHAT WOULD HAVE TAKEN THE
ARMORY TEAM AT JUPITER STATION

597
00:31:30,222 --> 00:31:31,807
AT LEAST A WEEK.

598
00:31:31,849 --> 00:31:35,477
TO SAY THAT I'M PROUD OF THEM
WOULD BE AN UNDERSTATEMENT.

599
00:31:35,519 --> 00:31:38,480
WE'RE PREPARING OUR FIRST TEST.

600
00:31:38,522 --> 00:31:41,149
EVERYBODY HAS
THEIR FINGERS CROSSED,

601
00:31:41,191 --> 00:31:42,860
INCLUDING ME.

602
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,656
ARCHER: YOU'RE SURE
THERE'S NOTHING DOWN THERE?

603
00:31:47,698 --> 00:31:49,658
T'POL: YES, CAPTAIN.
ARCHER: NOT EVEN A MICROBE?

604
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:51,493
I DON'T WANT TO BLOW UP
SOMETHING THAT COULD EVOLVE

605
00:31:51,535 --> 00:31:54,079
INTO A SENTIENT SPECIES
IN A COUPLE OF BILLION YEARS.

606
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:56,122
T'POL: THERE'S NOTHING THERE.

607
00:31:56,164 --> 00:31:59,167
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
ARCHER TO LIEUTENANT REED.

608
00:31:59,209 --> 00:32:00,419
HAVE YOU GOT A LOCK?

609
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:01,628
Reed: Yes, Captain.

610
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:03,630
LET'S START SMALL.

611
00:32:03,672 --> 00:32:06,592
SHAVE A COUPLE OF METERS
OFF THE TOP OF THAT PEAK.

612
00:32:06,633 --> 00:32:08,594
ACQUIRING THE TARGET.

613
00:32:08,635 --> 00:32:10,596
[ BEEPING ]

614
00:32:10,637 --> 00:32:13,098
FULL POWER TO THE PRIMARY COILS.

615
00:32:20,439 --> 00:32:23,316
PHASE CANNONS ONE AND TWO
STANDING BY.

616
00:32:24,484 --> 00:32:26,445
MR. REED...

617
00:32:26,486 --> 00:32:28,947
THE HONOR IS ALL YOURS.

618
00:32:42,210 --> 00:32:44,797
I JUST ASKED
FOR A LITTLE OFF THE TOP!

619
00:32:44,838 --> 00:32:46,465
-CHECK THE CANNONS!
-YES, SIR.

620
00:32:46,506 --> 00:32:48,425
BE CAREFUL DOWN THERE.

621
00:32:48,467 --> 00:32:51,845
THE BLAST YIELD
WAS 10 TIMES WHAT WE EXPECTED.

622
00:32:51,887 --> 00:32:53,430
Archer: What happened?

623
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:56,475
SOMETHING OVERLOADED
THE PHASE MODULATORS.

624
00:32:56,516 --> 00:32:59,185
THE PLASMA RECOIL BLEW OUT
RELAYS ACROSS DECKS "C" AND "D."

625
00:32:59,227 --> 00:33:02,230
I'M GETTING AN ANOMALOUS
READING FROM LAUNCH BAY 2.

626
00:33:02,272 --> 00:33:04,983
TRIP, T'POL.

627
00:33:27,881 --> 00:33:29,424
TUCKER: THERE.

628
00:33:29,466 --> 00:33:31,134
WHAT'S THAT?

629
00:33:32,761 --> 00:33:35,388
ARCHER: YOU THINK THAT'S WHAT'S
CAUSING THE POWER SURGE?

630
00:33:35,430 --> 00:33:37,390
T'POL: IT'S VERY LIKELY.

631
00:33:37,432 --> 00:33:40,477
IT'S PUTTING OUT
A TREMENDOUS AMOUNT OF ENERGY,

632
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:43,438
OVER 600 MEGAJOULES.

633
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:46,107
REED: THEY'RE TOYING WITH US.

634
00:33:46,149 --> 00:33:49,110
THEY WANT US TO KNOW THEY CAN
DESTROY US WHENEVER THEY WANT,

635
00:33:49,152 --> 00:33:51,697
EVEN WITH OUR OWN WEAPONS.

636
00:33:51,738 --> 00:33:53,281
T'POL: WHATEVER IT IS,

637
00:33:53,323 --> 00:33:55,325
IT'S TAPPED INTO MOST
OF OUR SYSTEMS,

638
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:59,371
INCLUDING INTERNAL SENSORS AND
COMMUNICATIONS ON EVERY DECK.

639
00:34:03,792 --> 00:34:05,377
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

640
00:34:05,418 --> 00:34:09,631
ACTIVATE VISUAL SENSOR J-15.

641
00:34:09,673 --> 00:34:11,633
<i>I ASSUME</i>
<i>YOU PLANTED THAT DEVICE</i>

642
00:34:11,675 --> 00:34:14,845
<i>BECAUSE YOU WANTED</i>
<i>TO LEARN MORE ABOUT US.</i>

643
00:34:16,638 --> 00:34:19,307
<i>I'LL BE HAPPY TO GIVE YOU</i>
<i>A QUICK LESSON.</i>

644
00:34:19,349 --> 00:34:22,227
<i>WE'RE NOT HERE TO MAKE ENEMIES.</i>

645
00:34:22,268 --> 00:34:24,813
<i>BUT JUST BECAUSE</i>
<i>WE'RE NOT LOOKING FOR A FIGHT</i>

646
00:34:24,855 --> 00:34:27,900
<i>DOESN'T MEAN</i>
<i>WE'LL RUN AWAY FROM ONE.</i>

647
00:34:27,941 --> 00:34:30,903
<i>YOU MAY THINK</i>
<i>YOU'VE LEFT US DEFENSELESS,</i>

648
00:34:30,944 --> 00:34:33,947
<i>BUT LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING</i>
<i>ABOUT HUMANS.</i>

649
00:34:33,989 --> 00:34:36,909
<i>WE DON'T GIVE UP EASILY.</i>

650
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:40,119
<i>WE'LL PROTECT</i> ENTERPRISE...

651
00:34:43,040 --> 00:34:45,124
<i>ANY WAY WE CAN.</i>

652
00:34:51,006 --> 00:34:52,883
DOCTOR?

653
00:34:52,925 --> 00:34:55,552
PHLOX: I'LL BE WITH YOU
IN A MOMENT, ENSIGN.

654
00:34:55,594 --> 00:34:58,137
HOSHI: I SEE YOU RELEASED
YOUR PATIENTS.

655
00:34:58,179 --> 00:35:00,390
PHLOX: HMM.
THEY'RE GOING TO BE FINE.

656
00:35:00,432 --> 00:35:02,392
I SENT THEM BACK
TO THEIR QUARTERS TO REST.

657
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:04,436
HOSHI: THAT'S GOOD TO HEAR.

658
00:35:06,438 --> 00:35:08,481
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

659
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:12,402
YOU SPEND A LOT OF TIME
IN THE MESS HALL.

660
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:14,446
HAVE YOU EVER HAD A MEAL
WITH LIEUTENANT REED?

661
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:16,406
PHLOX: MANY TIMES.

662
00:35:16,448 --> 00:35:19,618
ANY IDEA WHAT
HIS FAVORITE FOOD MIGHT BE?

663
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:23,580
AH, THE BIRTHDAY DINNER. HMM.

664
00:35:23,622 --> 00:35:26,165
UH, WELL, THE MAN LOVES
A GOOD BREAKFAST.

665
00:35:26,207 --> 00:35:27,751
-LIKE WHAT?
-EGGS.

666
00:35:27,793 --> 00:35:29,461
I'VE SEEN HIM EAT
A LOT OF EGGS.

667
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:30,670
HOSHI: HOW DOES HE LIKE THEM?

668
00:35:30,712 --> 00:35:33,548
OH, SCRAMBLED, POACHED,
OVER EASY.

669
00:35:33,590 --> 00:35:37,094
MAYBE CHEF COULD MAKE HIM
A...BIG OMELET.

670
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:39,721
OH, AND HE ENJOYS PANCAKES,
ON OCCASION. HMM.

671
00:35:39,763 --> 00:35:42,307
HE HAS THE ODD HABIT OF
SPREADING PEANUT BUTTER ON THEM.

672
00:35:42,348 --> 00:35:44,350
UH, SAUSAGE--
THAT'S ANOTHER FAVORITE--

673
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:45,978
AND BACON, TOO,
COME TO THINK OF IT.

674
00:35:46,019 --> 00:35:49,314
IS THERE ANY ONE FOOD
IN PARTICULAR?

675
00:35:49,355 --> 00:35:52,985
HMM...NOT THAT I RECALL.

676
00:35:55,695 --> 00:35:58,115
BREAKING A VULCAN
ENCRYPTION CODE

677
00:35:58,156 --> 00:36:00,033
WOULD BE EASIER THAN THIS.

678
00:36:00,075 --> 00:36:02,661
PHLOX: IF ANYTHING COMES
TO MIND, I'LL, UH, LET YOU KNOW.

679
00:36:02,702 --> 00:36:05,580
HOSHI: I DON'T SUPPOSE SCANNING
HIS TASTE BUDS WOULD HELP?

680
00:36:05,622 --> 00:36:08,667
MEDICALLY SPEAKING, THERE'S
NO ACCOUNTING FOR TASTE.

681
00:36:08,708 --> 00:36:10,669
HOSHI: THANKS, ANYWAY.

682
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:12,378
PHLOX: MM-HMM.

683
00:36:13,588 --> 00:36:14,881
BROMELIN!

684
00:36:14,923 --> 00:36:16,299
SORRY?

685
00:36:16,341 --> 00:36:17,676
I THINK I CAN HELP YOU, ENSIGN.

686
00:36:17,717 --> 00:36:19,594
[ PHLOX CHUCKLES ]

687
00:36:19,636 --> 00:36:23,640
BUT IT, UH, WOULD MEAN GOING
INTO MR. REED'S MEDICAL RECORDS.

688
00:36:23,682 --> 00:36:25,600
THAT INFORMATION
IS CONFIDENTIAL.

689
00:36:25,642 --> 00:36:28,394
HOSHI: I'M UNDER DIRECT ORDERS
FROM THE CAPTAIN.

690
00:36:29,938 --> 00:36:32,899
COULDN'T YOU MAKE AN EXCEPTION?

691
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:35,944
PHLOX: UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
I SUPPOSE IT WOULDN'T HURT.

692
00:36:35,986 --> 00:36:37,946
HMM.

693
00:36:37,988 --> 00:36:38,738
AH.

694
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:40,490
AH.

695
00:36:40,532 --> 00:36:43,702
I'VE MADE IT A POINT TO STUDY
EACH CREWMAN'S MEDICAL HISTORY,

696
00:36:43,743 --> 00:36:45,912
AND I REMEMBER NOTICING
THAT LIEUTENANT REED

697
00:36:45,954 --> 00:36:47,873
SUFFERS FROM A NUMBER
OF ALLERGIES.

698
00:36:47,914 --> 00:36:52,544
LET'S SEE--DUST MITES, OAK,
POLLEN, TROPICAL GRASSES.

699
00:36:52,585 --> 00:36:54,504
AH! HA HA HA!
HERE IT IS.

700
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:59,176
HE'S AVERSE TO VARIOUS PLANT
ENZYMES, INCLUDING BROMELIN.

701
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,844
HOSHI: WHAT DOES ALL
OF THIS HAVE TO DO WITH

702
00:37:00,886 --> 00:37:02,470
WHAT HE LIKES TO EAT?

703
00:37:02,512 --> 00:37:04,139
PHLOX: OVER THE LAST
SEVERAL YEARS, HE'S BEEN TAKING

704
00:37:04,181 --> 00:37:07,809
REGULAR INJECTIONS SO THAT HIS
BODY CAN TOLERATE BROMELIN.

705
00:37:07,851 --> 00:37:09,769
A PLANT ENZYME...

706
00:37:09,811 --> 00:37:11,980
-YES.
-FOUND IN...

707
00:37:12,022 --> 00:37:14,691
PHLOX: AMONG OTHER THINGS,
PINEAPPLE.

708
00:37:14,733 --> 00:37:16,651
HOSHI: PINEAPPLE.

709
00:37:16,693 --> 00:37:19,320
THIS DOESN'T MEAN
IT'S HIS FAVORITE FOOD.

710
00:37:19,362 --> 00:37:22,115
IT'S CLOSE ENOUGH.
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

711
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:24,201
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

712
00:37:29,998 --> 00:37:31,124
[ BEEPING ]

713
00:37:31,166 --> 00:37:33,001
-IT'S THEM.
-WHERE ARE THEY?

714
00:37:33,043 --> 00:37:35,045
T'POL: CLOSING FROM ASTERN--

715
00:37:35,087 --> 00:37:36,671
20,000 METERS.

716
00:37:36,713 --> 00:37:37,923
15,000.

717
00:37:37,964 --> 00:37:40,217
MAYWEATHER: SHOULD I TRY
EVASIVE MANEUVERS?

718
00:37:40,258 --> 00:37:44,137
NO. COME ABOUT
AND HOLD OUR POSITION.

719
00:37:44,179 --> 00:37:46,139
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
BRIDGE TO THE ARMORY.

720
00:37:46,181 --> 00:37:47,640
GUESS WHO'S BACK.

721
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:48,892
REED: WE SEE THEM.

722
00:37:48,934 --> 00:37:51,436
BOTH FORWARD CANNONS
ARE CHARGED AND READY.

723
00:37:51,477 --> 00:37:52,979
ARCHER: GET A LOCK AND STAND BY.

724
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:54,439
T'POL: THEY'VE STOPPED.

725
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:56,149
11,000 METERS.

726
00:37:56,191 --> 00:37:57,901
WE'RE BEING HAILED.

727
00:37:57,943 --> 00:37:59,152
PUT IT THROUGH.

728
00:38:00,195 --> 00:38:01,696
<i>ARCHER'S VOICE: ...DEFENSELESS.</i>

729
00:38:01,738 --> 00:38:02,989
<i>PREPARE TO SURRENDER</i>
<i>YOUR VESSEL.</i>

730
00:38:03,031 --> 00:38:05,784
<i>YOU ARE DEFENSELESS.</i>
<i>PREPARE TO...</i>

731
00:38:05,825 --> 00:38:07,077
SHUT IT OFF.

732
00:38:07,119 --> 00:38:09,495
<i>YOU ARE DEFENS--</i>

733
00:38:09,537 --> 00:38:11,497
MAYWEATHER: 10,000 METERS.

734
00:38:11,539 --> 00:38:13,125
9,000.

735
00:38:13,166 --> 00:38:15,127
MR. REED...

736
00:38:15,168 --> 00:38:17,295
BOTH CANNONS, FIRE.

737
00:38:26,179 --> 00:38:28,306
I'M READING A FLUCTUATION
IN THEIR SHIELDING,

738
00:38:28,347 --> 00:38:30,349
BUT IT'S MARGINAL.

739
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:31,559
5,000 METERS.

740
00:38:31,601 --> 00:38:33,603
IS THAT THE BEST WE CAN DO,
LIEUTENANT?!

741
00:38:33,645 --> 00:38:35,563
EVEN IF THESE CANNONS HAD BEEN
INSTALLED AT JUPITER STATION,

742
00:38:35,605 --> 00:38:37,899
THEY WOULDN'T BE ANY MORE
EFFECTIVE THAN THEY ARE NOW.

743
00:38:37,941 --> 00:38:39,400
Archer: What about yesterday?

744
00:38:39,442 --> 00:38:41,402
I saw you blow something up
the size of Mount McKinley.

745
00:38:41,444 --> 00:38:44,072
YES, SIR, BUT THAT WAS DUE
TO AN OVERLOAD.

746
00:38:45,907 --> 00:38:47,826
CAN YOU OVERLOAD THEM AGAIN?

747
00:38:47,867 --> 00:38:50,328
SIR, AFTER THE DAMAGE
FROM THE FIRST TIME,

748
00:38:50,369 --> 00:38:52,998
THE PLASMA RECOIL WILL PROBABLY
KNOCK OUT TWO DECKS.

749
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:54,833
CAN YOU OVERLOAD THEM AGAIN?!

750
00:38:54,874 --> 00:38:56,501
REED: I BELIEVE SO, BUT...

751
00:38:56,542 --> 00:38:59,296
I'D RATHER KNOCK OUT TWO DECKS
THAN SURRENDER THIS SHIP.

752
00:38:59,337 --> 00:39:01,214
-BUT, SIR...
-HOLD ON A MINUTE.

753
00:39:01,256 --> 00:39:02,882
I THINK THERE'S A WAY
TO HANDLE THE RECOIL.

754
00:39:02,924 --> 00:39:04,550
-How?
-All that excess energy's

755
00:39:04,592 --> 00:39:05,760
got to go somewhere.

756
00:39:05,802 --> 00:39:07,971
-WHY NOT PUT IT TO USE?
-3,000 meters.

757
00:39:08,013 --> 00:39:10,598
IF WE REPOLARIZE THE GRAVITY
PLATING TO ABSORB THE RECOIL,

758
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:12,642
THEN WE CAN SHUNT THE ENERGY
TO STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY.

759
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:14,227
SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

760
00:39:14,269 --> 00:39:15,520
THE GRAV-PLATING WASN'T DESIGNED

761
00:39:15,561 --> 00:39:17,105
TO WITHSTAND THAT MUCH FORCE.

762
00:39:17,147 --> 00:39:19,398
WE ALL UNDERSTAND THE RISKS.
GET STARTED.

763
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:21,400
Reed: Aye, sir.

764
00:39:25,989 --> 00:39:27,199
[ BEEPING ]

765
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:28,658
MAYWEATHER: 1,000 METERS.

766
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:29,909
MALCOLM?

767
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:31,995
STAND BY.

768
00:39:33,538 --> 00:39:34,956
TRIP?

769
00:39:36,958 --> 00:39:38,584
WE'RE READY, SIR.

770
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:40,628
THEN FIRE!

771
00:39:51,223 --> 00:39:52,431
[ BEEPING ]

772
00:39:52,473 --> 00:39:54,267
THEIR SHIELDS ARE FAILING.

773
00:39:54,309 --> 00:39:55,727
TORPEDOES!

774
00:40:25,965 --> 00:40:27,926
ARCHER: BRIDGE TO THE ARMORY.

775
00:40:27,967 --> 00:40:29,886
EVERYTHING OK DOWN THERE?

776
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:31,637
TUCKER: WE BLEW OUT
THE PLASMA RELAYS ON B-DECK,

777
00:40:31,679 --> 00:40:33,598
BUT IT'S NOTHING
WE CAN'T TAKE CARE OF.

778
00:40:33,639 --> 00:40:34,891
WHAT ABOUT OUR FRIENDS?

779
00:40:34,933 --> 00:40:36,475
Archer: I have a feeling

780
00:40:36,517 --> 00:40:39,562
THEIR REPAIRS ARE GONNA BE
A LITTLE MORE EXTENSIVE.

781
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:41,273
Archer: How'd the cannons
hold up?

782
00:40:41,314 --> 00:40:42,732
REED: FAIRLY WELL.

783
00:40:42,774 --> 00:40:44,859
Reed: I'll have them back online
within the hour.

784
00:40:44,901 --> 00:40:47,820
THE AFT CANNON SHOULD BE WORKING
BY THE END OF DAY TOMORROW.

785
00:40:47,862 --> 00:40:49,530
GOOD WORK.

786
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:54,035
WELL...

787
00:40:55,995 --> 00:41:00,917
I SEE NO REASON FOR US TO GO
BACK TO JUPITER STATION NOW...

788
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:02,877
DO YOU?

789
00:41:02,919 --> 00:41:04,837
T'POL: NO.

790
00:41:04,879 --> 00:41:06,547
HOSHI: AT LEAST THERE'S
ONE GOOD THING

791
00:41:06,589 --> 00:41:08,133
ABOUT COMING BACK THIS FAR--

792
00:41:08,174 --> 00:41:10,593
WE CAN DROP
ANOTHER SUBSPACE AMPLIFIER.

793
00:41:11,970 --> 00:41:13,096
GET ON IT.

794
00:41:22,021 --> 00:41:24,065
TRAVIS?

795
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,986
RESUME OUR PREVIOUS COURSE.

796
00:41:28,027 --> 00:41:29,988
MAYWEATHER: GLADLY, SIR.

797
00:41:30,029 --> 00:41:31,323
[ BEEPING ]

798
00:41:36,619 --> 00:41:38,537
TUCKER: TO OUR
MYSTERIOUS FRIENDS.

799
00:41:38,579 --> 00:41:40,581
I WISH I COULD'VE SEEN
THE LOOKS ON THEIR FACES.

800
00:41:40,623 --> 00:41:42,708
REED: HEAR, HEAR.
[ TUCKER CHUCKLES ]

801
00:41:45,753 --> 00:41:47,588
ARCHER: DON'T GET TOO USED
TO DRINKING ON DUTY...

802
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:49,174
[ CHUCKLING ]

803
00:41:49,215 --> 00:41:52,760
BUT YOU DID YOUR JOBS
PRETTY DAMN WELL YESTERDAY.

804
00:41:52,802 --> 00:41:55,638
I'D SAY THAT DESERVES
A LITTLE CELEBRATION.

805
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:57,349
REED: CHEERS.

806
00:42:00,518 --> 00:42:02,479
TUCKER: IF YOU REALLY
WANT TO THANK US,

807
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:04,522
HOW ABOUT LETTING US
SLEEP IN TOMORROW?

808
00:42:04,563 --> 00:42:06,483
[ LAUGHTER ]

809
00:42:06,565 --> 00:42:09,152
PERMISSION GRANTED.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

810
00:42:09,194 --> 00:42:11,112
HOSHI, WHAT CAN WE DO FOR YOU?

811
00:42:11,154 --> 00:42:13,114
HOSHI: SORRY TO INTERRUPT,
CAPTAIN.

812
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:15,992
I HAVE THAT COMPONENT
THAT YOU ASKED FOR.

813
00:42:16,034 --> 00:42:18,119
GREAT.
PUT IT DOWN RIGHT HERE.

814
00:42:19,454 --> 00:42:20,955
HMM.

815
00:42:20,997 --> 00:42:24,125
AS LONG AS WE'VE GOT YOU HERE,
MALCOLM...

816
00:42:26,461 --> 00:42:28,129
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

817
00:42:28,171 --> 00:42:30,215
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE GONE
TO ANY TROUBLE.

818
00:42:30,256 --> 00:42:33,301
ARCHER: NO, NO TROUBLE AT ALL.

819
00:42:35,220 --> 00:42:38,306
MR. REED,
THE HONOR IS YOURS.

820
00:42:53,279 --> 00:42:55,365
PINEAPPLE!

821
00:42:55,407 --> 00:42:57,116
THAT'S MY FAVORITE.

822
00:42:58,493 --> 00:43:00,953
HOW ON EARTH DID YOU KNOW?

823
00:43:02,330 --> 00:43:04,916
HOSHI: WE HAVE OUR SOURCES.
